r, horizontal. The combination is what makes the Cross.', 1397, 0), (461484, 'I remember my mom bought me one of their shirts for Easter so that I could wear Helmut Lang for Easter. That was my first piece.', 69239, 0), (461485, 'I don''t really care what people tell children - when you believe in Santa Claus, the Easter Bunny and the Tooth Fairy, one more fib won''t hurt. But I am infuriated by the growing notion, posited in some touchy-feely quarters, that all women are, or can be, beautiful.', 28504, 0), (461486, 'Each year in early spring, during the season of Lent, which begins on Ash Wednesday and concludes on Easter, a plenitude of books, magazine articles, and television shows about Jesus appear.', 50301, 0), (461487, 'In the past, I''ve visited remote places - North Korea, Ethiopia, Easter Island - partly as a way to visit remote states of mind: remote parts of myself that I wouldn''t ordinarily explore.', 711, 0), (461488, 'Most people outside of America won''t get it. It''s the Easter bunny. It''s another lie and I don''t understand why we had to invent this character.', 67058, 0), (461489, 'My mom used to say that Greek Easter was later because then you get stuff cheaper.', 274, 0), (461490, 'Even if you''re not Christian, just from being in our culture you know Jesus and resurrection and redemption.', 6876, 0), (461491, 'Easter is one of my favorite holidays with the kids. They get to run loose, and we always have our family and loved ones all around us!', 67873, 0), (461492, 'People come together with their families to celebrate Easter. What better way to celebrate than to spend a few hours going on the journey of Christ''s life.', 36603, 0), (461493, 'For those of you who still believe in the Easter Bunny and that the letters that appear in your local newspaper come from concerned citizens who really care, I''ve got troubling news. At least in politics, most of the letters that get published on the letters-to-the-editor page originate in the campaign headquarters of the candidates.', 67884, 0), (461494, 'Fortunately, the DC Universe is full enough and replete enough with every kind of character that you could want, that it''s not that hard to find the right character. Sometimes it''s nothing more than an Easter egg, or a name drop, and sometimes it''s someone like ''Deathstroke,'' who is a huge part of the DC Universe.', 73332, 0), (461495, 'At one time I smoked, but in 1959 I couldn''t think of anything else to give up for Lent so I stopped - and I haven''t had a cigarette since.', 70274, 0), (461496, 'Christ appeared alive on several occasions after the cataclysmic events of that first Easter.', 44170, 0), (461497, 'Winning the 2007 Master''s was a dream fulfilled culminating on Easter Sunday with my family was very special. You couldn''t write it up any better.', 72687, 0), (461498, 'I had my boy in Boston on Easter Sunday. That kills me, from a sports perspective. He''s a Boston baby and I''m a New York guy.', 69383, 0), (461499, 'Let every man and woman count himself immortal. Let him catch the revelation of Jesus in his resurrection. Let him say not merely, ''Christ is risen,'' but ''I shall rise.''', 22130, 0), (461500, 'Do we believe that there is equal economic opportunity out there in the real world, right now, for each and every one of these groups? If we believed in the tooth fairy, if we believed in the Easter Bunny, we might well believe that.', 73333, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (461501, 'I cooked at the White House for Easter, last year, with Michelle Obama. But it more had to do with cooking from the organic garden, and her message. I took my daughter and granddaughter there, and they were really charming, it was great.', 43897, 0), (461502, 'I read the Scriptures at the American Cathedral on Christmas and Easter that''s it. It''s a task I love.', 70307, 0), (461503, 'Between the three, Facebook is literally everyone I''ve ever shaken hands with at a conference or kissed on the cheek at Easter. Twitter seems to be everyone I am entertained by or I wish to meet some day. Foursquare seems to be everyone I run into on a regular basis. All three of those social graphs are powerful in their own.', 69300, 0), (461504, 'I was raised - and still consider myself to be - Catholic, though I''m non-practicing and haven''t fulfilled my Easter duty since sometime during the Nixon years. I''m assailed by all kinds of stimulating doubts, but I do believe in God.', 5480, 0), (461505, 'God expects from men something more than at such times, and that it were much to be wished for the credit of their religion as well as the satisfaction of their conscience that their Easter devotions would in some measure come up to their Easter dress.', 63015, 0), (461506, 'To a Christian, Easter Sunday means everything, when we celebrate the resurrection of Jesus Christ.', 71409, 0), (461507, 'Passover and Easter are the only Jewish and Christian holidays that move in sync, like the ice skating pairs we saw during the winter Olympics.', 68782, 0), (461508, 'My passion was to be on Broadway and to be part of this community because I saw what it was like from the outside as the young kid in and around New York, and I would see things like the ''Easter Bonnet'' or ''Broadway Bares,'' things I would sneak into.', 73334, 0), (461509, 'What makes you a Christian is whether or not you really are in accord with biblical theology and whether you know Jesus Christ as your Saviour.', 73335, 0), (461510, 'And it is always Easter Sunday at the New York City Ballet. It is always coming back to life. Not even coming back to life - it lives in the constant present.', 2748, 0), (461511, 'I am very proud of this work because it is more about the meaning of the Easter Rising and its relationship to what this whole century has been about, people liberating themselves, freeing themselves.', 9729, 0), (461512, 'To see how Christ was prophesied and described therein, consider and mark, how that the kid or lamb must be with out spot or blemish; and so was Christ only of all mankind, in the sight of God and of his law.', 44167, 0), (461513, '''Rapa Nui'' is about the conflict in the 1600s on Easter Island. It''s about the clash of the royal clan and the working class.', 73336, 0), (461514, 'When you ran out the tunnel at the old Easter Road for a derby game, you''d get a spittal right on the back of your head. They were spitting on you as you ran out, which actually helped get you going. It was some place.', 72041, 0), (461515, 'I''m Jewish, so I don''t know much about Easter eggs.', 73337, 0), (461516, 'All I ask is the chance to prove that money can''t make me happy.', 7873, 0), (461517, 'The biggest risk is not taking any risk... In a world that changing really quickly, the only strategy that is guaranteed to fail is not taking risks.', 5553, 0), (461518, 'To reminisce with my old friends, a chance to share some memories, and play our songs again.', 73338, 0), (461519, 'Growth is never by mere chance it is the result of forces working together.', 51966, 0), (461520, 'Every year on your birthday, you get a chance to start new.', 73339, 0), (461521, 'Being brave means to know something is scary, difficult, and dangerous, and doing it anyway, because the possibility of winning the fight is worth the chance of losing it.', 445, 0), (461522, 'Forgiveness says you are given another chance to make a new beginning.', 2109, 0), (461523, 'You have to take risks. We will only understand the miracle of life fully when we allow the unexpected to happen.', 34, 0), (461524, 'If you are not willing to risk the unusual, you will have to settle for the ordinary.', 1295, 0), (461525, 'There are risks and costs to action. But they are far less than the long range risks of comfortable inaction.', 1680, 0), (461526, 'America is the land of the second chance - and when the gates of the prison open, the path ahead should lead to a better life.', 2358, 0), (461527, 'People do make mistakes and I think they should be punished. But they should be forgiven and given the opportunity for a second chance. We are human beings.', 30010, 0), (461528, 'The world is so unpredictable. Things happen suddenly, unexpectedly. We want to feel we are in control of our own existence. In some ways we are, in some ways we''re not. We are ruled by the forces of chance and coincidence.', 496, 0), (461529, 'If you go around being afraid, you''re never going to enjoy life. You have only one chance, so you''ve got to have fun.', 68105, 0), (461530, 'Freedom is nothing but a chance to be better.', 532, 0), (461531, 'The risk of a wrong decision is preferable to the terror of indecision.', 1858, 0), (461532, 'First, I have to thank God for giving me the gift that he did as well as a second chance for a better life.', 72398, 0), (461533, 'If you don''t love the Dodgers, there''s a good chance you may not get into Heaven.', 5198, 0), (461534, 'Destiny is no matter of chance. It is a matter of choice. It is not a thing to be waited for, it is a thing to be achieved.', 17514, 0), (461535, 'Just keep taking chances and having fun.', 56259, 0), (461536, 'I guess I''m pretty much of a lone wolf. I don''t say I don''t like people at all, but, to tell you the truth, I only like it then if I have a chance to look deep into their hearts and their minds.', 15789, 0), (461537, 'Anytime we step out boldly to make changes, we take a chance that we might fail. But the only way to get better is to try.', 1206, 0), (461538, 'If you take no risks, you will suffer no defeats. But if you take no risks, you win no victories.', 9695, 0), (461539, 'It''s choice - not chance - that determines your destiny.', 29810, 0), (461540, 'Take a chance! All life is a chance. The man who goes farthest is generally the one who is willing to do and dare.', 1005, 0), (461541, 'Beware of missing chances otherwise it may be altogether too late some day.', 22699, 0), (461542, 'Filmmaking is a chance to live many lifetimes.', 64420, 0), (461543, 'Refugees come to us seeking asylum, seeking freedom, justice and dignity - seeking a chance just to breathe. And people in our country are saying close the doors and don''t let them in?', 34499, 0), (461544, 'If somebody is gracious enough to give me a second chance, I won''t need a third.', 63429, 0), (461545, 'Chance is always powerful. Let your hook always be cast; in the pool where you least expect it, there will be fish.', 782, 0), (461546, 'If we choose to walk into a forest where a tiger lives, we are taking a chance. If we swim in a river where crocodiles live, we are taking a chance. If we visit the desert or climb a mountain or enter a swamp where snakes have managed to survive, we are taking a chance.', 13539, 0), (461547, 'If by chance some day you''re not feeling well and you should remember some silly thing I''ve said or done and it brings back a smile to your face or a chuckle to your heart, then my purpose as your clown has been fulfilled.', 62651, 0), (461548, 'My sole ambition is to rid Mexico of the class that has oppressed her and given the people a chance to know what real liberty means. And if I could bring that about today by giving up my life, I would do it gladly.', 73340, 0), (461549, 'Atheism is so senseless. When I look at the solar system, I see the earth at the right distance from the sun to receive the proper amounts of heat and light. This 