ake it for $7 million, then everybody can have a chance to make a little bit of money, and you get to make the film you want to make.', 73353, 0), (461639, 'The criteria for serving one''s country should be competence, courage and willingness to serve. When we deny people the chance to serve because of their sexual orientation, we deprive them of their rights of citizenship, and we deprive our armed forces the service of willing and capable Americans.', 33473, 0), (461640, 'Evil is an attack against human spiritual development and enlightenment. All evil, badness, neurosis - it has one motive and one motive only, which is to destroy - to destroy your chance of arising above yourself.', 1508, 0), (461641, 'I''ve got big shoes to fill. This is my chance to do something. I have to seize the moment.', 2245, 0), (461642, 'If you call yourself a leader, then you have to be decisive. If you''re decisive, then you have the chance to be a leader. These are two sides to the same coin.', 40212, 0), (461643, 'We are able to find everything in our memory, which is like a dispensary or chemical laboratory in which chance steers our hand sometimes to a soothing drug and sometimes to a dangerous poison.', 450, 0), (461644, 'Wealthy men can''t live in an island that is encircled by poverty. We all breathe the same air. We must give a chance to everyone, at least a basic chance.', 31997, 0), (461645, 'You''re not going to eliminate concussions. Anytime you hit your head, you have a chance of getting a concussion, in any sport, too. I think we have to learn more about it. Part of it is rules, part of it is equipment, part of it is medical studies, knowing more about the brain.', 13024, 0), (461646, 'Give peace a chance.', 21741, 0), (461647, 'Luck, that''s when preparation and opportunity meet.', 17477, 0), (461648, 'The more I come to know about the outside world''s perception of China, the more I feel there are all sorts of misunderstandings, and to a certain extent, people do not get the full picture from the media. A lot of foreigners have few opportunities to visit China, and a lot of Chinese people do not have the chance to go to Europe or to the West.', 66598, 0), (461649, 'When it comes to luck, you make your own.', 2251, 0), (461650, 'Most of us regard good luck as our right, and bad luck as a betrayal of that right.', 5249, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (461651, 'Our lives improve only when we take chances - and the first and most difficult risk we can take is to be honest with ourselves.', 42554, 0), (461652, 'It is not like I have gone crazy, I just don''t want to take any chances. You never know what could happen.', 28287, 0), (461653, 'Luck is always the last refuge of laziness and incompetence.', 51966, 0), (461654, 'Man, when I''m riding with the helmet on, I''m invisible. And people just deal with me as the guy on the bike... it gives you a chance to read ''em.', 2614, 0), (461655, 'I have been trying to point out that in our lives chance may have an astonishing influence and, if I may offer advice to the young laboratory worker, it would be this - never to neglect an extraordinary appearance or happening.', 59256, 0), (461656, 'Give yourself a chance to see how much better life will get. And it will get better.', 73354, 0), (461657, 'It''s so much worse to live in regret in your forties than it is to take a chance in your late twenties.', 73355, 0), (461658, 'I call on people to be ''obsessed citizens,'' forever questioning and asking for accountability. That''s the only chance we have today of a healthy and happy life.', 20064, 0), (461659, 'We all have big changes in our lives that are more or less a second chance.', 12392, 0), (461660, 'If proud Americans can be who they are and boldly stand at the altar with who they love then surely, surely we can give everyone in this country a fair chance at that great American Dream.', 1997, 0), (461661, 'I like to travel any chance I get, even if it''s just a local vacation to San Diego or Palm Springs or wherever. I just like to get out and do stuff and see the world.', 73356, 0), (461662, 'I figure you have the same chance of winning the lottery whether you play or not.', 1437, 0), (461663, 'But to me the bottom line is the more education you can give yourself, and the more preparation you can do, the less chance of failing.', 73357, 0), (461664, 'People often remark that I''m pretty lucky. Luck is only important in so far as getting the chance to sell yourself at the right moment. After that, you''ve got to have talent and know how to use it.', 10463, 0), (461665, 'The public health of five million children should not be left to luck or chance.', 15479, 0), (461666, 'If the sun comes up, I have a chance.', 37889, 0), (461667, 'Walking at random through the streets, we came by chance upon the Cathedral of Notre Dame. I shall long remember my first impression of the scene within. The lofty gothic ceiling arched far above my head and through the stained windows the light came but dimly - it was all still, solemn and religious.', 57546, 0), (461668, 'All the evidence shows very clearly that if you are a member of a trade union you are likely to get better pay, more equal pay, better health and safety, more chance to get training, more chance to have conditions of work that help if you have caring responsibilities... the list goes on!', 71321, 0), (461669, 'Those who seek to profit by division don''t stand a chance.', 68, 0), (461670, 'It comes from the likes of you! Take what you can get! Grab the chances as they come along! Act in hallways! Sing in doorways! Dance in cellars!', 60508, 0), (461671, 'When a person cannot deceive himself the chances are against his being able to deceive other people.', 286, 0), (461672, 'Your chances of success in any undertaking can always be measured by your belief in yourself.', 10101, 0), (461673, 'I have the freedom to take chances, to say no. I have the freedom to be who I really want to be, rather than have to conform to this or that just to stay alive.', 20594, 0), (461674, 'People are lucky and unlucky not according to what they get absolutely, but according to the ratio between what they get and what they have been led to expect.', 4111, 0), (461675, 'One hour of life, crowded to the full with glorious action, and filled with noble risks, is worth whole years of those mean observances of paltry decorum, in which men steal through existence, like sluggish waters through a marsh, without either honor or observation.', 972, 0), (461676, 'Care and diligence bring luck.', 1348, 0), (461677, 'I haven''t lived a perfect life. I have regrets. But that''s from a lifetime of taking chances, making decisions, and trying not to be frozen. The only thing that I can do with my regrets is understand them.', 36742, 0), (461678, 'I just do whatever it is that I believe I should do, regardless of the risks to my life.', 67376, 0), (461679, 'At some point in your life, if you''re lucky, you get to design the way in which things evolve.', 73358, 0), (461680, 'Sometimes there are things worth risking your life for. It was Jesus who said if you want to save your life, you have to lose it.', 73359, 0), (461681, 'I don''t believe in pitfalls. I believe in taking risks and not doing the same thing twice.', 68163, 0), (461682, 'I tend to be a person who starts with the presumption that I should trust you until you abuse the privilege, and then our relationship is forever changed. That''s a very big line, and chances are it''s not going to work if it''s crossed. I warn people that this is how I''m going to deal with it.', 73360, 0), (461683, 'I see retirement as just another of these reinventions, another chance to do new things and be a new version of myself.', 69340, 0), (461684, 'No foreign policy - no matter how ingenious - has any chance of success if it is born in the minds of a few and carried in the hearts of none.', 2393, 0), (461685, 'Fame is like a shaved pig with a greased tail, and it is only after it has slipped through the hands of some thousands, that some fellow, by mere chance, holds on to it!', 65656, 0), (461686, 'Improvisation is too good to leave to chance.', 1017, 0), (461687, '''Eyes Wide Open'' took shape from two real life events straight from my own past. One was the sad suicide of my young nephew, a troubled kid, who was found at the bottom of a landmark cliff in central California. The second was a chance encounter forty years ago with none other than, ahem, Charles Manson!', 55588, 0), (461688, 'For me, conferences are like little mental vacations: a chance to go visit an interesting place for a couple of days, and come back rested and refreshed with new ideas and perspectives.', 3740, 0), (461689, 'The goal of Dr. Martin Luther King is to give Negroes a chance to sit in a segregated restaurant beside the same white man who had brutalized them for 400 years.', 1730, 0), (461690, 'Here is the root of all romanticism: that man, the individual, is an infinite reservoir of possibilities, and if you can so rearrange society by the destruction of oppressive order, then these possibilities will have a chance, and you will get Progress.', 51297, 0), (461691, 'The universe is so unique and perfect that it could not have originated by chance but was divined by flawless, creative design.', 42858, 0), (461692, 'It''s one of my favorite seasons of the year: Back to School. As a kid, I loved fresh school supplies, new outfits, the change of seasons, and the chance to crack open a new textbook.', 61931, 0), (461693, 'For the happiest life, days should be rigorously planned, nights left open to chance.', 1932, 0), (461694, 'The successful man is the one who had the chance and took it.', 64987, 0), (461695, 'Neither can men, by the same principles, be considered as lands, goods, or houses, among possessions. It is necessary that all property should be inferiour to its possessor. But how does the slave differ from his master, but by chance?', 73361, 0), (461696, 'When you''re a chef, you graze. You never get a chance to sit down and eat. They don''t actually sit down and eat before you cook. So when I finish work, the first thing I''ll do, and especially when I''m in New York, I''ll go for a run. And I''ll run 10 or 15k on my - and I run to gain my appetite.', 49687, 0), (461697, 'Credit card companies are jacking up interest rates, lowering credit limits, and closing accounts - and people who have made timely payments are not exempt. So even if you pay off your balance - and that''s tough when interest rates are insanely high - there''s a good chance your credit limit will be slashed, and that will hurt your FICO score.', 10090, 0), (461698, 'If everybody is doing it one way, there''s a good chance you can find your niche by going exactly in the opposite direction.', 34844, 0), (461699, 'I always leave room for serendipity and chance.', 73362, 0), (461700, 'No man was ever wise by chance.', 65434, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (461701, 'The great thing about suicide is that it''s not one of those things you have to do now or you lose your chance. I mean, you can always do it later.', 1025, 0), (461702, 'If what I do prove well, it won''t advance. They''ll say it''s stolen, or else it was by chance.', 1211, 0), (461703, 'In my mind''s eye, I visualize how a particular... sight and feeling will appear on a print. If it excites me, there is a good chance it will make a good photograph. It is an intuitive sense, an ability that comes from a lot of practice.', 1347, 0), (461704, 'A person who has not done one half his day''s work by ten o clock, runs a chance of leaving the other half undone.', 55, 0), (461705, 'If you have a dream, give it a chance to happen.', 46601, 0), (461706, 'Why if I had half a chance, I could make an entire movie using this stock footage. The story opens on these mysterious explosions. Nobody knows what''s causing them, but it''s upsetting all the buffalo. So, the military are called in to solve the mystery.', 44272, 0), (461707, 'The 50-50-90 rule: Anytime you have a 50-50 chance of getting something right, there''s a 90% probability you''ll get it wrong.', 1350, 0), (461708, 'The Christians had a better chance against the lions than the American consumer has against the OPEC cartel.', 67414, 0), (461709, 'I think this is one of the greatest strengths of this school. Not only do the students go on to achieve great milestones in their own lives, they never forget their roots and the school that gave them the chance they needed to improve their lives and their families'' lives.', 70643, 0), (461710, 'There''s only one test of a great children''s book, or a great children''s film, and that is this: If it can be read or viewed with pleasure by adults, then it has the chance to be a great children''s film, or a great children''s book.', 19844, 0), (461711, 'The team is completely close. Anything you say outside, there is no chance it will go inside. So the team is really strong and compact. We know what we want and how to achieve it on the pitch.', 43297, 0), (461712, 'It seemed to me that this might be a great pageant, which would give a chance for a very interesting picture.', 73363, 0), (461713, 'Chance makes our parents, but choice makes our friends.', 24636, 0), (461714, 'Before the first year, nobody gave it a chance. Now, 36 years later, everybody knows Monday Night Football.', 65798, 0), (461715, 'Success is not assured, but America is resolute: this is the best chance for peace we are likely to see for some years to come - and we are acting to help Israelis and Palestinians seize this chance.', 25026, 0), (461716, 'All anyone asks for is a chance to work with pride.', 11418, 0), (461717, 'Any time you take a chance you better be sure the rewards are worth the risk because they can put you away just as fast for a ten dollar heist as they can for a million dollar job.', 7875, 0), (461718, 'The value of the majority lies not in the opportunity to wield great power, but in the chance to use power to do great things.', 66633, 0), (461719, 'I don''t care what other people think as long as I am happy. The day I die or retire, I have blown all my chances because I don''t have the chance any more to change my image as an F1 driver.', 73364, 0), (461720, 'To me, the stand up part in my life is great. I know I can do that. When I get an acting chance, I''m really thrilled.', 53024, 0), (461721, 'In the theatre you can change things ever so slightly; it''s an organic thing. Whereas in film you only have that chance on the day, and you have no control over it at all.', 72208, 0), (461722, 'Now we Democrats believe that America is still the country of fair play, that we can come out of a small town or a poor neighborhood and have the same chance as anyone else, and it doesn''t matter whether we are black or Hispanic, or disabled or women.', 12192, 0), (461723, 'It''s not that people don''t like classical music. It''s that they don''t have the chance to understand and to experience it.', 70310, 0), (461724, 'As for Guns N'' Roses, I don''t think there''s ever a chance of a reunion.', 22833, 0), (461725, 'Falling in love, romance, matters of the heart - when you fall in love, on some biochemical level you know there is a chance it won''t work out. It''s ingrained in us that if you take such an enormous risk on someone with your heart that it might not pay off. I gamble all my chips and I might actually lose everything.', 70818, 0), (461726, 'My whole story is just about me having a second chance.', 73365, 0), (461727, 'I think my thing is I grew up in the ghetto, and I was able to get a second chance. That''s what I''m trying to tell kids.', 73366, 0), (461728, 'When we have peace, then we have a chance to save the planet. But if we are not united in peace, if we do not practice mindful consumption, we cannot save our planet.', 394, 0), (461729, 'Liverpool has always made me brave, choice-wise. It was never a city that criticised anyone for taking a chance.', 73159, 0), (461730, 'I am proof that one person can rise above any challenge, and if I can, then so will others if they are given the chance.', 33422, 0), (461731, 'My life experience has taught me nothing happens by chance. Even the idea of the ball in a roulette game: it''s not chance it ends up in a certain place. It''s forces that are at play.', 67812, 0), (461732, 'The more completely we focus our attention on our Creator and Lord, the less chance there is of our being distracted by creatures.', 70538, 0), (461733, 'I love baseball. The game allowed me the influence to impact kids in a positive way. This gives me a chance to talk to some social issues.', 72583, 0), (461734, 'Unless you burst into movies as a sex goddess, you''re likely to play wives and mothers. I came into movies as a teenager in ''They Shoot Horses, Don''t They'' (1969) playing a pregnant waif from the Ozarks. I didn''t get a chance to burst into movies in ''Body Heat.'' My career isn''t based on having a 23-inch waist and a big bust, though I do.', 73367, 0), (461735, 'The insurance of working with a big, already successful franchise just gives you the chance to do other things on a more personal level.', 68421, 0), (461736, 'I have warned many times about the guaranteed dangers of betting with your heart instead of your head - big darkness, soon come - but every once in a while you get a fair chance to have it both ways, and the annual NCAA basketball Tournament is one of them.', 126, 0), (461737, 'I feel a real sense of duty to use the voice and the platform I''ve been afforded by my fame to speak out for those whose voices don''t get a chance to be heard.', 67847, 0), (461738, '''Park Avenue: Money, Power and the American Dream'' is an intentionally angry film. How could it not be when the chance of an infant dying is five times greater on the Bronx Park Avenue than on Manhattan''s Park Avenue just across the Harlem River?', 46335, 0), (461739, 'I think that if you have a knack for storytelling, and you work really hard at it, you''ll have a chance to tap into something deep. But the fact remains that good sentences are hard won. Any writer worth a lick knows constructing a sentence, a paragraph, or a chapter is hard work.', 22295, 0), (461740, 'When I won the Golden Gloves in 1960, that made me realize I had a chance. And when I won at the Olympics, that sealed it: I was the champ.', 1751, 0), (461741, 'Give ordinary folk the chance to buy the same things as rich people.', 34844, 0), (461742, 'The Savior isn''t our last chance He is our only chance. Our only chance to overcome self-doubt and catch a vision of who we may become. Our only chance to repent and have our sins washed clean.', 70492, 0), (461743, 'I eat at In-N-Out Burger every chance I get.', 70666, 0), (461744, 'Risk it; go for it. Life always gives you another chance, another go at it. It''s very important to take enormous risks.', 57412, 0), (461745, 'There''s a short chain between field and fork, and the shorter that chain is - the fresher, the more transparent that system is - the less chance there is of anything from bio-terrorism to pathogenicity to spoilage.', 2536, 0), (461746, 'We try to create a situation where we''re the casino. It''s like how an actuary would set insurance rates. Predictability, predictability, predictability. What''s the path to least risk? What''s the greater chance of getting some return on this asset?', 66698, 0), (461747, 'I''d never taken a job purely for money - I felt that would kill me - but I was afraid that I was heading that way. Then, my brother passing away was the final thing that kicked me over. It reminded me that life is short, and you''d better do what you want while you have a chance.', 67788, 0), (461748, 'When you are just starting out with an online business, there''s a good chance that you''ll be making several mistakes. Because of the mistakes that can be made with starting an online business, many people decide to quit or think that online businesses are just a scam.', 19591, 0), (461749, 'There is always some chance of recession in any year. But the evidence suggests that expansions don''t die of old age.', 69500, 0), (461750, 'I wanted to - any chance I had to dress up as a boy, like Halloween, I would be a pirate or a ghost that wore a tie. A hobo.', 68248, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (461751, 'I got this second chance at life, and I live it.', 68264, 0), (461752, 'Creative non-fiction is such a liberating genre because it allows the non-fiction writer, whether he or she be journalist or essayist, to use all of the techniques of the fiction writer and all of the ideas, creative approaches, that fiction writers get a chance to use, but they have to use it in a true story.', 53822, 0), (461753, 'The whole life of an American is passed like a game of chance, a revolutionary crisis, or a battle.', 4021, 0), (461754, 'A consistent soul believes in destiny, a capricious one in chance.', 1827, 0), (461755, 'Every possession and every happiness is but lent by chance for an uncertain time, and may therefore be demanded back the next hour.', 1304, 0), (461756, 'Treat all men alike. Give them the same law. Give them an even chance to live and grow.', 4664, 0), (461757, 'My grandmother spent her whole life working as a maid, a cook and a babysitter, barely scraping by, but still working hard to give my mother, her only child, a chance in life, so that my mother could give my brother and me an even better one.', 68134, 0), (461758, 'Dances have a second and third life. You feel they are never ready. They always have a chance for another life.', 56814, 0), (461759, 'If you have the chance to be exposed to a loving, understanding environment where the seed of compassion, loving kindness, can be watered every day, then you become a more loving person.', 69092, 0), (461760, 'I don''t even know how to speak up for myself, because I don''t really have a father who would give me the confidence or advice. And if you''re always the new kid, you never get a chance to adapt, so your confidence is just zilch.', 392, 0), (461761, 'The former colonies, in Latin America in particular, have a better chance than ever before to overcome centuries of subjugation, violence and foreign intervention, which they have so far survived as dependencies with islands of luxury in a sea of misery.', 1955, 0), (461762, 'I really don''t like the gym. I like experiences, so I take any chance I get to go on a bicycle or on a hike.', 38496, 0), (461763, 'Short of hiring a new staff, consider giving subpar workers a chance to improve. Tell them why they''re not measuring up and give them a set amount of time to make specific improvements.', 66636, 0), (461764, 'We''ve heard the excuses from those responsible for hiring that they don''t want to take a chance on a new director. But the truth is that the industry hires new directors all the time it''s just that most of them are white males.', 73368, 0), (461765, 'I actually hated dancing. My mum used to have to bribe me to go by buying me things. A year before I stopped going, I was going to go for an audition with the Royal Ballet. It turned out I was a year too young. Because I was tall, they thought I was older. But before I had the chance to go back, I quit.', 71242, 0), (461766, 'I''m actually an evangelical atheist, but there is something I recognise about religion: that it gives people a chance to surrender.', 18504, 0), (461767, 'The great opportunity belongs to him who can see it, to him who can grasp it. The better part of your chance is right inside of you.', 4025, 0), (461768, 'As a comedian, you want people to like you. That''s part of why you''re there in the first place: You have this unquenchable need to be liked, and then when you divert from that and take a chance at doing something that has moments of fierce unlikeability, you can hit some real low points.', 15814, 0), (461769, 'Voting shouldn''t be a challenge. It should be as easy and accessible as possible. We shouldn''t require forms of ID that folks don''t have. We shouldn''t restrict days or hours that allow working people a chance to both do their job and exercise their democratic right, and we damn well shouldn''t be throwing up new obstacles midstream.', 67006, 0), (461770, 'A lot of people head into courtship looking for fireworks. Don''t pass up a chance by dumping someone after a first date because you don''t feel the fireworks. The fireworks can happen at any time and be maintained.', 52746, 0), (461771, 'When you''re the host of the Academy Awards, and you grew up watching Bob Hope and Johnny Carson, and now it''s your turn, and you get a chance to run with the baton on the relay for a while, I really embraced it and just really loved being there.', 22849, 0), (461772, 'Man, who is he? Too bad, to be the work of God: Too good for the work of chance!', 217, 0), (461773, 'In front of us was not a line but a fortress position, twenty miles deep, entrenched and fortified, defended by masses of machine-gun posts and thousands of guns in a wide arc. No chance for cavalry!', 68790, 0), (461774, 'What makes creative people tingle are interesting problems, the chance to impress their friends, and caffeine.', 30506, 0), (461775, 'I''d love to make a movie with Tom Hardy. If we ever got the chance to make a Venom movie together, that would be super-cool, but his movie would have to take place in the MCU because I''m not giving up my ticket in the MCU.', 20849, 0), (461776, 'Great deeds are usually wrought at great risks.', 1863, 0), (461777, 'A wise man turns chance into good fortune.', 1348, 0), (461778, 'I just love to play and I get a chance to play with other musicians and I jump on it.', 68565, 0), (461779, 'All human beings are born entrepreneurs. Some get a chance to unleash that capacity. Some never got the chance, never knew that he or she has that capacity.', 3626, 0), (461780, 'At 9 years old, I moved in with my father because my mother could no longer care for me. Looking back, I now see so many similarities between my own childhood and that of my sons. My father stepped in when I needed him, and that gave me the chance for a better life. That''s what I''m doing for my boys now.', 68367, 0), (461781, 'It''s been a struggle for me because I had a chance to be white and refused.', 2259, 0), (461782, 'You can''t sit on a lead and run a few plays into the line and just kill the clock. You''ve got to throw the ball over the damn plate and five the other man his chance. That''s why baseball is the greatest game of them all.', 61066, 0), (461783, 'A pound of pluck is worth a ton of luck.', 44653, 0), (461784, 'We are given to the cult of personality; when things go badly we look to some messiah to save us. If by chance we think we have found one, it will not be long before we destroy him.', 73369, 0), (461785, 'Beset by a difficult problem? Now is your chance to shine. Pick yourself up, get to work and get triumphantly through it.', 34033, 0), (461786, 'Remember to be gentle with yourself and others. We are all children of chance and none can say why some fields will blossom while others lay brown beneath the August sun.', 5155, 0), (461787, 'I am constantly struggling to show people that there is more to me than my appearance. You do have to try and overcome those hurdles. Female actresses need to be given the chance to be more than how they look.', 52565, 0), (461788, 'With commentating, I''ve had a chance to show the humorous side of my personality that I didn''t use on the court. It''s fun, and I don''t take myself too seriously. I have good broadcast teams with me, but I''m not a huge stats guy. I think they post the numbers too quickly, and I''d rather let the match play out a bit first.', 63558, 0), (461789, 'One must not make oneself cheap here - that is a cardinal point - or else one is done. Whoever is most impertinent has the best chance.', 611, 0), (461790, 'You know, from my point of view, I''m the luckiest cat on the planet.', 38121, 0), (461791, 'If you are given a chance to be a role model, I think you should always take it because you can influence a person''s life in a positive light, and that''s what I want to do. That''s what it''s all about.', 11163, 0), (461792, 'It is true that the Puritans banned all recreation on Sundays and all games of chance, gambling, bear baiting, horse racing, and bowling in or around taverns at all times. They did so, not because they were opposed to fun, but because they judged these activities to be inherently harmful or immoral.', 14149, 0), (461793, 'We really only have two choices. Play it safe, or take a chance. For me, pulling back because of fear has always made me feel worse.', 30206, 0), (461794, 'A child-like man is not a man whose development has been arrested; on the contrary, he is a man who has given himself a chance of continuing to develop long after most adults have muffled themselves in the cocoon of middle-aged habit and convention.', 1032, 0), (461795, 'Always go to the bathroom when you have a chance.', 68759, 0), (461796, 'To God be humble, to thy friend be kind, and with thy neighbors gladly lend and borrow; His chance tonight, it maybe thine tomorrow.', 69106, 0), (461797, '''Chance the Rapper'' is many things. I''m constantly evolving.', 67776, 0), (461798, 'There''s a way of playing safe, there''s a way of using tricks and there''s the way I like to play which is dangerously where you''re going to take a chance on making mistakes in order to create something you haven''t created before.', 64810, 0), (461799, 'I''ve always taken risks, and never worried what the world might really think of me.', 863, 0), (461800, 'The flower has opened, has been in the sun and is unafraid. I''m taking more chances; I''m bold and proud.', 72299, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (461801, 'Over the years, I''ve come to recognize that democratization in Ethiopia is not just a matter of choice. It''s a matter of national survival. I am deeply convinced that we either democratize and have a good chance of surviving, or if we fail to do so, we disintegrate.', 67163, 0), (461802, 'I''ve had a chance to fly a lot of different airplanes, but it was nothing like the shuttle ride.', 2061, 0), (461803, 'If one has curiosity, then one stands the chance of attain a high level of scientific inquiry.', 71069, 0), (461804, 'Marathon running, like golf, is a game for players, not winners. That is why Callaway sells golf clubs and Nike sells running shoes. But running is unique in that the world''s best racers are on the same course, at the same time, as amateurs, who have as much chance of winning as your average weekend warrior would scoring a touchdown in the NFL.', 126, 0), (461805, 'When it comes to the American dream, no one has a corner on the market. All of us have an equal chance to share in that dream.', 67449, 0), (461806, 'Not to get too deep on shaving my mustache, but it was kind of symbolic of, ''This is a moment of liberation, a chance to reinvent yourself.'' That''s kind of what I did.', 70449, 0), (461807, 'I was a freshman All-American, and I tore my ACL in the third game. But God has a plan for everything. I had a chance to turn away from Him in that situation or draw closer to Him. I decided to draw closer to Him, and came back stronger from it.', 69641, 0), (461808, 'While there is a chance of the world getting through its troubles, I hold that a reasonable man has to behave as though he were sure of it. If at the end your cheerfulness in not justified, at any rate you will have been cheerful.', 3173, 0), (461809, 'If I had a chance for another life, I would certainly choose a better complexion.', 72793, 0), (461810, '''The Slap'' is not like anything else. It''s an incredibly well-written novel that has been turned into a great and intriguing series that reveals both less and more about each character than you learn in the book. It''s a novel that has been given a second chance to live.', 69143, 0), (461811, 'They decided to let immigrants in and I am an immigrant. They gave us a chance to participate in this country''s life and I took it.', 1135, 0), (461812, 'I''m proud to be part of the Dr. Pepper Scholarship Giveaway. It''s a great program that gives me the chance to brighten the day for some lucky college students with free tuition.', 2081, 0), (461813, 'For me, take Tiger Woods. I always thought he was great, but I never truly understood how good he was until I had the chance to go to Tiger Woods Golf Camp. He taught me how to swing and was hitting the ball, and this dude was unreal.', 73370, 0), (461814, 'Poker is a skill game pretending to be a chance game.', 20595, 0), (461815, 'I''m all about taking chances. You have to ask yourself, if you''re not taking any chances, are you actually even living? Every time you walk out of your door and you''re out in the world, you take a chance on not coming back. That is the danger and the dynamic of being alive.', 58187, 0), (461816, 'The chance of any species reaching and then surviving on an island as distant as one of the Hawaiian chain is infinitesimal, but despite the extraordinary odds, plants and seeds found their way ashore, carried by the tide or blown by trade winds, inside birds or in their feathers, in the branches of trees and in the jetsam of sunken ships.', 73371, 0), (461817, 'My father will anticipate everything. He will leave you and me no chance to do a great and brilliant deed.', 7819, 0), (461818, 'If the girl is good looking and talented, and for some reason the film doesn''t work, she gets a second chance. But if subsequent films don''t work, she gets branded as an ''iron leg.'' The whole thing gets negative.', 68929, 0), (461819, 'I prefer to be alive, so I''m cautious about taking risks.', 2043, 0), (461820, 'I believe in luck: how else can you explain the success of those you dislike?', 2343, 0), (461821, 'God''s dice always have a lucky roll.', 139, 0), (461822, 'I am a free spirit. I am very impulsive. I put the most trust in people chance after chance, regardless of how they treat me.', 68226, 0), (461823, 'No man ever wetted clay and then left it, as if there would be bricks by chance and fortune.', 4891, 0), (461824, 'When I get a chance to play golf or go on a boat with good people, take the boat out and put some lobsters on the grill, get the ice-cold beer and the cigars - that''s heaven here on earth.', 68423, 0), (461825, 'A property in the 100-year floodplain has a 96 percent chance of being flooded in the next hundred years without global warming. The fact that several years go by without a flood does not change that probability.', 73372, 0), (461826, 'I run an academy in Spain for young footballers who are released by their clubs and who, in my opinion, deserve a second chance. It is a rewarding job for me, but one that also reveals many of the faults in the English game.', 71455, 0), (461827, 'It is not about the money. It''s the public service aspect. Absolutely, I think it has qualities of redemption. The city gets a second chance. I get a second chance.', 72568, 0), (461828, 'My mom and dad put my brother and sister through university and they were very keen for us to have an academic background just to give us a chance.', 72069, 0), (461829, 'I''m going to write a book, continue acting, continue motivational speaking and just share with people who I am and what I''ve learned in my second chance of life and pass it on to people in their first chance of life.', 73373, 0), (461830, 'I''ve had a chance to see something that is way outside everybody else''s frame of reference and gives a perspective that is very different from everyone else''s.', 2061, 0), (461831, 'If Donald Trump is our nominee, I don''t think that he represents the best our party has to offer either in temperament or qualification, and I think he''s the weakest candidate that is in the race at this point in terms of the general election, and that to nominate him is to give Hillary Clinton a much better chance of being president.', 72123, 0), (461832, 'I want a president with a record of public service: someone whose life''s work shows our children that we don''t chase form and fortune for ourselves we fight to give everyone a chance to succeed. ', 1997, 0), (461833, 'In college I never realized the opportunities available to a pro athlete. I''ve been given the chance to meet all kinds of people, to travel and expand my financial capabilities, to get ideas and learn about life, to create a world apart from basketball.', 1813, 0), (461834, 'You hit home runs not by chance but by preparation.', 66712, 0), (461835, 'The chances of each of us coming into existence are infinitesimally small, and even though we shall all die some day, we should count ourselves fantastically lucky to get our decades in the sun.', 1716, 0), (461836, 'If someone is always to blame, if every time something goes wrong someone has to be punished, people quickly stop taking risks. Without risks, there can''t be breakthroughs.', 66565, 0), (461837, 'Thinking of Plan B muddies up your chances of succeeding at Plan A.', 43364, 0), (461838, 'No human being will ever know the Truth, for even if they happen to say it by chance, they would not even known they had done so.', 4027, 0), (461839, 'This club is all about winning trophies and we''ve got a chance of bringing the greatest trophy of them all back to Anfield, so it means a great deal obviously.', 73374, 0), (461840, 'Be strong and follow your own convictions. You can''t assume there is a lot of time to do what you like. This is what David Bowie is afraid of: that he will die before he gets a chance to make a real strong contribution.', 7292, 0), (461841, 'I just think that giving a child a chance and sharing what you have with a child is one of the greatest gifts you can give yourself, as well as a child.', 66567, 0), (461842, 'It''s good to have a lot of once-in-a-lifetimes in your lifetime. If you get the chance to skydive, go skydiving. If you''re offered a part in a weird Shakespeare play in San Diego, slap on some tights and rock out some iambic pentameter.', 36406, 0), (461843, 'You never know in TV - sometimes you''re on at the wrong time at the wrong place. Sometimes you don''t get a chance to catch on.', 71241, 0), (461844, 'No government ought to be without censors; and where the press is free, no one ever will. Chance is the pseudonym of God when he did not want to sign.', 348, 0), (461845, 'My intention here is to make it clear that not a single cell of my composition, here in regard to The Raven, is found by chance or intuition, that the composition moved towards perfection with the precision and inevitability of a mathematical equation.', 30040, 0), (461846, 'The fundamental problem with program maintenance is that fixing a defect has a substantial chance of introducing another.', 73375, 0), (461847, 'Events are not a matter of chance.', 73376, 0), (461848, 'There''s nothing more exciting for an actor than a chance to lose, to be someone who has lost - especially if it''s someone who starts off with a veneer of control. To be broken is wonderful.', 72470, 0), (461849, 'Chance determines our lives in important ways.', 31108, 0), (461850, 'If people are given the chance to experience life in more than one country, they will hate a little less. It''s not a miracle potion, but little by little you can solve problems in the basement of a country, not on the surface.', 2030, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (461851, 'To be honest, I never really considered myself to be too much of an actress. So, whenever I get the chance to do music, I''m always, like, just in it. It''s like, ''Oh my God, I finally get to do this. I''m so happy.''', 52532, 0), (461852, 'Good economic theory must give the people the chance to use their talents to build their own lives. We must get away from the traditional route where the rich will do the business and the poor will depend on private or public charity.', 3626, 0), (461853, 'Man, if I get a chance to speak on the microphone, I''ve got to say something somewhere in there. You know, I''m going to laugh and have fun, too, but something has to be said that has some substance, because this is a platform, and the power that we have with words and with this microphone is phenomenal.', 55313, 0), (461854, 'You can lay in bed and think you don''t stand a chance, that''s what all of us thought, and here we are. We ended up doing all right.', 12979, 0), (461855, 'In books, as in life, there are no second chances. On second thought: it''s the next work, still to be written, that offers the second chance.', 30964, 0), (461856, 'Birth is violent, and out of that violence is our only chance of rebirth.', 68943, 0), (461857, 'This is a truth that should be repeated like a mantra: to have any chance of a ful - filling life, we require not only clean air and a steady climate, but also an abundance of meadows and woodlands, rivers and oceans, teeming with life and the mass existence of other living creatures.', 12852, 0), (461858, 'I''d call my work ''instinctual design.'' I like to find the spirit of a piece that defies time, age, and occasion. My clothes give the wearer the chance to develop their own voice within a wardrobe, and I think of them as curators of their personal style.', 67999, 0), (461859, 'In Japan, usually, once you become prime minister, you do not have a second chance.', 67426, 0), (461860, 'I''ve told myself I have a chance to make history, and that''s my focus.', 73377, 0), (461861, 'You got to make the most of your second life. I was born Nayvadius, but now I''m Future. Should I dwell on what Nayvadius was supposed to be? I get a chance to experience life as something else. I wasn''t supposed to be like this.', 68174, 0), (461862, 'It''s not like I''m looking for a blonde or a brunette, light-skinned or dark-skinned. I feel like I give any girl a fighting chance.', 72717, 0), (461863, 'Success can allow you to try for greatness, can give you an opportunity to take a chance on something. I''m very blessed to have the success that I''ve had, and that''s given me so many opportunities to work on being great.', 68239, 0), (461864, 'There is no chance and anarchy in the universe. All is system and gradation. Every god is there sitting in his sphere.', 760, 0), (461865, 'The Polynesians used to have a system where they proclaimed a fishing area as ''taboo.'' If any fisherman was caught fishing in a taboo area, they would be killed. The Polynesians understand that the fish had to be given a chance to recover.', 21274, 0), (461866, 'Those who trust to chance must abide by the results of chance.', 4110, 0), (461867, 'A very small cause which escapes our notice determines a considerable effect that we cannot fail to see, and then we say that the effect is due to chance.', 30572, 0), (461868, 'The circle of the return to birth can only remain open, but this is a chance, a sign of life, and a wound.', 2768, 0), (461869, 'When you learn about the teaching and the practice of another tradition, you always have a chance to understand your own teaching and practice.', 394, 0), (461870, 'It''s funny, because in 1970 I met the Beatles quite by a chance at a party. It was the Beethoven bicentenary, and I was then also playing the Beethoven Sonatas. And that''s all they wanted to hear about - I wanted to talk about them, and all they wanted to talk about was Beethoven.', 60415, 0), (461871, 'I like entrepreneurial people I like people who take risks.', 4882, 0), (461872, 'If you are living a life that feels right to you, if you''re willing to take creative chances or a creative path that feels like it''s mostly in keeping with your sensibilities, you know, aesthetic and artistic, then that''s what matters.', 15995, 0), (461873, 'I think the harder you work, the more luck you have.', 72650, 0), (461874, 'Taking risks gives me energy.', 65518, 0), (461875, 'The golden opportunity you are seeking is in yourself. It is not in your environment; it is not in luck or chance, or the help of others; it is in yourself alone.', 4025, 0), (461876, 'Being in a ship is being in a jail, with the chance of being drowned.', 2087, 0), (461877, 'If you keep saying things are going to be bad, you have a good chance of being a prophet.', 1467, 0), (461878, 'My biggest regret in life is that I didn''t hit John Denver in the mouth while I has the chance.', 17500, 0), (461879, 'It''s important to give it all you have while you have the chance.', 32889, 0), (461880, 'Going to college offered me the chance to play football for four more years.', 1727, 0), (461881, 'It is an eternal obligation toward the human being not to let him suffer from hunger when one has a chance of coming to his assistance.', 1662, 0), (461882, 'Joint undertakings stand a better chance when they benefit both sides.', 542, 0), (461883, 'An American cannot converse, but he can discuss, and his talk falls into a dissertation. He speaks to you as if he was addressing a meeting; and if he should chance to become warm in the discussion, he will say ''Gentlemen'' to the person with whom he is conversing.', 4021, 0), (461884, 'I never quit trying. I never felt that I didn''t have a chance to win.', 24450, 0), (461885, 'Fortunately, somewhere between chance and mystery lies imagination, the only thing that protects our freedom, despite the fact that people keep trying to reduce it or kill it off altogether.', 3667, 0), (461886, 'I think it''s important to take a break, you know, from the public eye for a while, and give people a chance to miss you. I want longevity. I don''t want to get out there and run myself ragged and spread myself thin.', 69258, 0), (461887, 'More than 100 people are involved in a transplant operation... and we can''t waste time and resources if there is a chance the caretakers aren''t up for an awesome responsibility.', 73378, 0), (461888, 'I parody myself every chance I get. I try to make fun of myself and let people know that I''m a human being, and these things that have happened to me are real. I''m not just some cartoon who exists and suddenly doesn''t exist.', 70112, 0), (461889, 'There are lots of things which I would love to tell him, but in some way, I also feel that I lost the person closest to me. And I got a second chance to live. So in a way I feel that I live for both of us... and I will do my best.', 73379, 0), (461890, 'I quit because I didn''t feel like the Detroit Lions had a chance to win. It just killed my enjoyment of the game.', 71921, 0), (461891, 'You know what I want? The answer is, I truly don''t know what I want. I don''t want to do a television series. I want to do dramas as well as comedies, but I have no idea what kind or in what order. Just give me the chance at them.', 1856, 0), (461892, 'There has been a huge advance in technology, which has improved the safety of the cars incredibly, but there are still some heavy crash impacts and in certain circumstances there is still the chance of fire today.', 73380, 0), (461893, 'If you want to treat China as an enemy, you have a much better chance of making them an enemy than if you treat them as a potential friend.', 73381, 0), (461894, 'Governments must give to all those who have hit life''s hurdles the chance to rebuild and have a future.', 66749, 0), (461895, 'I''ve always believed that the facts about dancing are more interesting than the myths, and this was a great chance for me to explore how the human body does such incredible things.', 73382, 0), (461896, 'It would make me feel that creative art has a chance in this crazy world that we all live in.', 71767, 0), (461897, 'In Kenya you''ve got the great birds and monkeys leaping through the trees overhead. It''s a chance to remember what the world is really like.', 67643, 0), (461898, 'So I picked a field where I had a little exposure. Where I thought I could have an enormous challenge, and have a chance to really do some good, to be a pioneer in an area, and not just be like everyone else.', 51791, 0), (461899, 'But you''ve reached them, and I''ve always wanted to reach people. I''m the first one to say I love my fans because they love that I took a chance.', 13020, 0), (461900, 'I cry every chance I get.', 71942, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (461901, 'Nobody owes anybody a living, but everybody is entitled to a chance.', 5448, 0), (461902, 'There are people who want to make men''s lives more difficult for no other reason than the chance it provides them afterwards to offer their prescription for alleviating life; their Christianity, for instance.', 11, 0), (461903, 'You have to make lots of birdies and give your opponent no chance.', 69803, 0), (461904, 'After the brain tumor happened, I realized I love acting, I''ve always loved it, I may never get a chance to do it again.', 67788, 0), (461905, 'It''s a werewolf movie with Christina Ricci, and it was a chance to work with some good people. But playing yourself is always fairly risky because you gotta watch how you goof on yourself.', 72323, 0), (461906, 'It took me six months to redeem myself at least to have another chance to at least have her get to know me and let her know I was at least a decent guy and to give me a shot. And here we are, we''ve been married seven years.', 53870, 0), (461907, 'I never thought I''d get a chance to do what I''m doing. It''s such a dream.', 73383, 0), (461908, 'I''ve never been someone that''s had a five-year plan, or a three-year plan. That just seems to lead to a lot of disappointment, and doesn''t give you the chance to be flexible.', 68462, 0), (461909, 'When we get a chance to take part in elections, I am ready to fight for leading positions, including in the presidential vote.', 73384, 0), (461910, 'For me, if God blessed me with that one great hit, I''m satisfied. But I''ve still got a lot in me, and I''d still like to get out there and tell a lot more stories cinematically. And God willing, I''ll get the chance to do that.', 71412, 0), (461911, 'At a time when nobody thought we''d ever see a new steel mill built in America, we took a chance and built one in a corn field in Indiana. Today Steel Dynamics is one of the largest steel producers in the United States.', 52321, 0), (461912, 'When I was younger, I would go to auditions to have the opportunity to audition, which would mean another chance to get up there and try out my stuff, or try out what I learned and see how it worked with an audience, because where are you gonna get an audience?', 761, 0), (461913, 'I''m a responsible soul. But anyone who has the chance to spend time with me can see I''m still 22 years old. I love talking about clothes and guys and shoes and makeup. Plus, I''m obsessed with anything Hello Kitty!', 67069, 0), (461914, 'When my father passed away, he had his organs donated. In that painful moment, I was deeply comforted knowing that my father would be able to give others a second chance at life. That is why I encourage everyone to sign up to be a donor.', 71381, 0), (461915, 'You''ve got a great chance in college to do all sorts of terrible irresponsible things, and you should totally do them. I mean, make huge mistakes. This is the time in your life if you screw up, it''s okay because you can bounce back from it.', 313, 0), (461916, 'You only get one chance at your life so why not jump cars?', 69655, 0), (461917, 'When I teach seminars, I tell people, ''Your stuff has to look like something that''s out there, because otherwise nobody will take a chance on you.''', 612, 0), (461918, 'Nobody has yet proven that taking a chance and doing something unique that an audience isn''t used to is a bad idea. What the theater lacks is that kind of courage.', 67678, 0), (461919, 'Despite the situation in Cuba, I had a chance to play on the national team; and compared to other baseball players and other people in Cuba, I had the opportunity to live at a level that was not very high class but in the middle.', 73385, 0), (461920, 'I am delighted to be joining ''Guardian U.S.''s team as a weekly columnist, and to have the chance to address American and global current events on its distinguished platform. ''Guardian U.S.'' brings the ''Guardian''s hard-hitting investigative brand to a new focus on American news and opinion.', 14555, 0), (461921, 'If you don''t have the good fortune to work a lot then you take any job you get offered, whether it''s a good job, fun job, a bad job, horrible job, whatever, you just take what you need to take. But I''m lucky in that - at the moment anyway and hopefully forever, but who knows - I get the chance to pick jobs for the kick of it and the fun.', 70221, 0), (461922, 'I have a novel that I can write. It''s about three soldiers from Somalia. Some babies have been disappearing up on 144th Street, and I speculate later on what happened to them and how they might have been got back. These guys are dead, all three, and they have a chance in the afterlife to do something they should have done when they were alive.', 14884, 0), (461923, 'A franchise is dictated on the success of doing one film right, so if you can get it done correctly, you''ve got a chance of something else, but sometimes it just doesn''t work that way. Ideally, it''s insurance for the future; if you can do something, if you can find a character that people really do like, then you''re very lucky.', 68421, 0), (461924, 'I don''t like rats, but there''s not much else I don''t like. The problem with rats is they have no fear of human beings, they''re loaded with foul diseases, they would run the place given half the chance, and I''ve had them leap out of a lavatory while I''ve been sitting on it.', 3969, 0), (461925, 'I feel more like I''m a person who has so much to offer in different capacities that it would be a danger for me not to give myself a chance to spread my wings in all different directions.', 558, 0), (461926, 'I thank Him every chance I get - on my knees praying.', 67024, 0), (461927, 'What I felt was, if you spend your life just writing fiction, you are going to falsify your material. And the fictional form was going to force you to do things with the material, to dramatize it in a certain way. I thought nonfiction gave one a chance to explore the world, the other world, the world that one didn''t know fully.', 14772, 0), (461928, 'While I''m more of a soccer and tennis fan myself, I still enjoying catching some football games when I get the chance.', 32425, 0), (461929, 'Hold puppies, kittens, and babies anytime you get the chance.', 63634, 0), (461930, 'I''m a chemistry guy. I believe you''ve got to play together to have a chance to win.', 73386, 0), (461931, 'Not to be too preachy, but I would really recommend to people, if you get the chance, to trust yourselves to leap without a net, because that will build the confidence. You know, you might shock yourself with how much you don''t need a net because you can catch yourself.', 69039, 0), (461932, 'As somebody who makes his living in the movie business and wants to contribute to it, I think that the best chance I have of doing that is just consistently working with great directors.', 51243, 0), (461933, 'With physical prep work, you know if you go to the gym, you will get size. There''s no chance it won''t happen. The emotional prep work is a variable. You could step onto the set one day and have a disconnect with your thoughts and feelings and have a rough day acting because you can''t quite tap into what you need.', 23824, 0), (461934, 'I quit my job in the bank when I was 19. I took a chance. I went to Milan to study opera and singing. My father really supported me economically.', 71362, 0), (461935, 'I always rewrite each day up to the point where I stopped. When it is all finished, naturally you go over it. You get another chance to correct and rewrite when someone else types it, and you see it clean in type. The last chance is in the proofs. You''re grateful for these different chances.', 110, 0), (461936, 'If you push down that pyramid of power and spread out the base, every member gets a chance to file their bill and have it heard and file their amendment and have it heard, as opposed to the system that we have now, which closes out, closes down bills, limits debate, and so forth.', 67566, 0), (461937, 'I tend to pick objectives that I feel are safe because I know that, in the moment, I always go for it. I have some rules for myself, though: Look for the rock faces without a lot of loose rock. Always rope up on glaciers where there is even a slight chance of falling into a crevasse. No pure free soloing. Never climb below hanging glaciers.', 47617, 0), (461938, 'Money is often a matter of chance or good fortune and is not the mark of a successful life. It is not the thing that brings a throb of pleasure or a thrill into my life. And I would not pose as a successful man if that were to be the measure.', 63087, 0), (461939, 'I am so grateful to Marc Jacobs, Riccardo Tisci, Karl Lagerfeld, and Katie Grand, who took a chance on me that first season and gave me an opportunity.', 68261, 0), (461940, 'I was thinking recently about the popularity of TV shows about people shopping for houses. I wonder if part of their appeal is the chance to vicariously imagine our lives playing out in a variety of spaces. We have a sense that the shape and style of our dwellings affects the shapes of the lives that unfold within them.', 31369, 0), (461941, 'Given a fair shot, given a fair chance, Americans have never, ever, ever, ever let their country down. Never. Never. Ordinary people like us. Who do extraordinary things.', 17532, 0), (461942, 'In many museums, you see one of this and one of that. You gain an understanding of what Abstract Expressionism or Minimalism is, but you aren''t given the chance to appreciate the mind of an artist.', 73387, 0), (461943, 'Standing on the apex of our planet is humbling. I''m starved of oxygen, depleted of reserves, unable to eat, and bound by anxiety. This is a dangerous place. Yet the symbolism of standing on top of the world gives me a chance to experience time on a cosmic scale.', 61808, 0), (461944, 'The next wave of the social graph is empowering services like Airbnb and Lyft that give people the chance to have that physical interaction. People are more open to that because of Airbnb. Airbnb took couch surfing and took an additional step.', 72493, 0), (461945, 'If you show emotion in competition, temporarily, you''ll be ineffective. If you''re disciplined enough, you don''t get down when you''re behind, and you have a chance to create something positive.', 14943, 0), (461946, 'I spent two summers working at Camp Curry and at Yosemite Lodge as a waiter. It gave me a chance to really be there every day - to hike up to Vernal Falls or Nevada Falls. It just took me really deep into it. Yosemite claimed me.', 20594, 0), (461947, 'I can''t be casual about losing. I always think I have a chance to win until winning is absolutely impossible.', 24450, 0), (461948, 'The American people are ready for solutions, and Donald Trump offers a chance to move in a new direction.', 66572, 0), (461949, 'When I was first diagnosed, I went out, as a book person, and got some books on cancer and looked up my version of the disease. It said that I had about a 5 percent chance of survival. I said, ''Gosh, well, it''s been a good run.'' What I didn''t realize is that in the two years since those books were published, things had shifted dramatically.', 2253, 0), (461950, 'If I wasn''t prepared knowing every year there is a huge chance of a fire that will require me to evacuate my property, then I''m an ignoramus. If people at this point don''t see that terrorism is a reality, and don''t take steps to prepare themselves a little more than they were the day before, then they are also an irresponsible ignoramus.', 67851, 0);
